ce.%3C%2Fli%3E%20%3Cli%3ERussian%20schools%20teach%20the%20value%20of%20%26quot%3Bself-sacrifice%2C%26quot%3B%20preparing%20children%20for%20martyrdom.%3C%2Fli%3E%20%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fabcnews.go.com%2FInternational%2Frussia-taking-heavy-losses-wages-new-offensive-ukraine%2Fstory%3Fid%3D104206675%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EUkraine%20says%20Russia%20lost%20more%20than%206%2C000%20soldiers%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20one%20week%20in%20its%20latest%20offensive%20trying%20to%20capture%20Avdiivka%2C%20a%20small%20city%20in%20eastern%20Ukraine.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThough%20it%20isn't%20possible%20to%20verify%20its%20figures%2C%20an%20%3Ca%20data-mrf-link%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2FDefenceHQ%2Fstatus%2F1715968466501472576%5C%22%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20nofollow%5C%22%20data-analytics-post-depth%3D%5C%2260%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2FDefenceHQ%2Fstatus%2F1715968466501472576%5C%22%20data-analytics-product-module%3D%5C%22body_link%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eintelligence%20update%3C%2Fa%3E%20from%20the%20UK%20Ministry%20of%20Defence%20estimates%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frussian-has-likely-suffered-480k-casualties-in-ukraine-uk-intel-2023-10%5C%22%3ERussian%20casualties%20since%20the%20invasion%20of%20Ukraine%20began%3C%2Fa%3E%20total%20290%2C000%20wounded%20or%20killed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20willingness%20of%20President%20Vladimir%20Putin%20and%20his%20generals%20to%20sacrifice%20thousands%20of%20soldiers%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Favdiivka-russia-losses-show-it-hasnt-learned-lessons-expert-2023-10%5C%22%3Eoften-reckless%20assaults%3C%2Fa%3E%20has%20become%20a%20blood-drenched%20hallmark%20of%20the%20war.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPeople%20who%20study%20Russia%20say%20war%20and%20a%20glorious%20death%20are%20ingrained%20in%20the%20Russian%20psyche%2C%20shaped%20by%20the%20collective%20memory%20of%20the%20extraordinary%20number%20%E2%80%94%20an%20estimated%2027%20million%20%E2%80%94%20in%20World%20War%20II.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPutin%20was%20born%20after%20the%20war%2C%20in%201952%2C%20but%20his%20family%20story%20in%20what%20Russia%20calls%20the%20Great%20Patriotic%20War%20echoes%20that%20of%20many%20Russian%20families%2C%20says%20Gregory%20Carleton%2C%20a%20professor%20of%20Russian%20studies%20at%20Tufts%20University.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BHis%20two%20uncles%20were%20killed%20on%20the%20front%20%E2%80%94%20his%20grandmother%20was%20shot%20by%20the%20Germans.%20His%20brother%20died%20from%20hunger%20and%20malnutrition.%20And%20his%20father%20was%20badly%20wounded%2C%26quot%3B%20Carleton%20told%20Insider.%20%26quot%3BSo%20in%20his%20own%20family%2C%20they've%20already%20paid%20that%20blood%20sacrifice%2C%20and%20he%20did%20his%20duty%20during%20the%20Cold%20War.%20So%20now%20it's%20very%20easy%20to%20call%20on%20the%20next%20generations.%20It's%20their%20turn%20to%20come%20in%20the%20cycle.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJaroslava%20Barbieri%2C%20a%20researcher%20into%20the%20role%20of%20the%20Russian%20state%20at%20Birmingham%20University%20in%20the%20UK%2C%20sees%20today's%20Kremlin%20under%20Putin%20as%20channeling%20and%20reinventing%20a%20Russian%20tradition%20that%20places%20a%20low%20value%20on%20an%20individual's%20life%20at%20the%20expense%20of%20the%20nation's%20destiny%2C%20reducing%20mobilized%2C%20untrained%20men%20to%20%26quot%3Bcannon%20fodder.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSo%20this%20complete%20disregard%20for%20individual's%20human%20life%20is%20evident%20from%20the%20Russian%20military's%20behavior%20on%20the%20battlefield%20where%20they%20just%20leave%20their%20dead%20bodies%20without%20collecting%20them%2C%20and%20bring%20them%20back%20home%20to%20their%20families%2C%26quot%3B%20Barbieri%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIndeed%2C%20on%20Friday%2C%20a%20Russian%20soldier%20said%20to%20be%20overheard%20in%20an%20intercepted%20phone%20call%20to%20his%20mother%20describing%20huge%20losses%20and%20a%20forest%20%26quot%3Bdotted%20with%20dead%20soldiers%26quot%3B%20during%20attempts%20to%20attack%20a%20village%20in%20eastern%20Ukraine.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere's%20such%20a%20slaughter%20going%20on%20there!%26quot%3B%20he%20says%20in%20the%20call%2C%20released%20by%20Ukraine's%20Military%20Intelligence%20Directorate%2C%20per%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.kyivpost.com%2Fpost%2F23337%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethe%20Kyiv%20Post%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20noted%20that%20it%20could%20not%20verify%20the%20call's%20legitimacy.%20%26quot%3BMore%20than%20a%20thousand%20were%20killed%20there.%20The%20first%20and%20second%20battalion%20was%20thrown%20forward%20%E2%80%94-%20there's%20a%20hell%20of%20a%20lot%20of%20200s%2C%20even%20more%20300s%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20continued%2C%20using%20military%20code%20for%20dead%20and%20wounded.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBen%20Soodavar%2C%20a%20researcher%20within%20the%20department%20of%20war%20studies%20at%20King's%20College%20London%2C%20recently%20wrote%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheconversation.com%2Fukraine-russias-losses-mount-but-self-sacrifice-in-war-is-part-of-the-countrys-mythology-215235%5C%22%3Eself-sacrifice%20in%20war%3C%2Fa%3E%20was%20part%20of%20Russian%20mythology%20and%20that%20the%20death%20of%20a%20soldier%20was%20%26quot%3Bfor%20Russia%20a%20step%20toward%20achieving%20the%20fantasy%20of%20national%20prestige.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20said%20that%20the%20trauma%20of%20military%20loss%20did%20not%20discourage%20Russians%20from%20fighting%20in%20Ukraine%20but%20was%20rather%20seen%20as%20a%20pathway%20to%20martyrdom.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EDeath%20'washes%20away%20all%20the%20sins'%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222666%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Russian%20soldiers%20march%20in%20unison%2C%20overseen%20by%20a%20senior%20military%20official.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F653a293796f7540cd06630af%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ERussian%20service%20members%20taking%20part%20in%20a%20military%20parade%20in%20Red%20Square%20on%20Victory%20Day%2C%20marking%20the%2078th%20anniversary%20of%20the%20victory%20over%20Nazi%20Germany%20in%20World%20War%20II.%3Cp%3EReuters%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ERussia's%20Orthodox%20Christianity%20has%20been%20coopted%20to%20glorify%20and%20elevate%20a%20death%20in%20battle.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20official%20mantra%20of%20the%20Russian%20military%20is%20John%2015%3A13%2C%20from%20the%20Bible%2C%26quot%3B%20Carleton%20said.%20%26quot%3BIt%20essentially%20says%2C%20There%20is%20no%20greater%20love%20than%20to%20give%20one's%20life%20for%20one's%20brother.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20theme%20emerged%20strongly%20in%C2%A0%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frussian-orthodox-leader-dying-in-war-a-sacrifice-absolves-sins-2022-9%3Fr%3DUS%26IR%3DT%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecomments%20by%20Patriarch%20Kirill%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20head%20of%20the%20Russian%20Orthodox%20Church%2C%20in%20September%202022%2C%20in%20which%20he%20was%20encouraging%20Russian%20men%20to%20join%20up%20and%20be%20killed%20%E2%80%94%20and%20be%20free%20of%20sin.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20a%20person%20dies%20in%20the%20performance%20of%20this%20duty%2C%20then%20they%20have%20undoubtedly%20committed%20an%20act%20equivalent%20to%20sacrifice%2C%26quot%3B%20Kirill%20said.%20%26quot%3BThey%20will%20have%20sacrificed%20themselves%20for%20others.%20And%20therefore%2C%20we%20believe%20that%20this%20sacrifice%20washes%20away%20all%20the%20sins%20that%20a%20person%20has%20committed.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3ESchoolchildren%20are%20taught%20to%20embrace%20the%20myth%20of%20self-sacrifice%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223240%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Children%20posing%20for%20a%20photo%20while%20holding%20a%20Russian%20flag%20and%20a%20pitchfork%20in%20front%20of%20a%20destroyed%20Ukrainian%20rocket%20launcher%20system.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F653a2a2596f7540cd06630f8%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222430%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EChildren%20pose%20on%20a%20destroyed%20Ukrainian%20Grad%20multiple%20rocket%20launcher%20system%20on%20public%20display%20at%20the%20central%20square%20in%20the%20occupied%20Ukrainian%20city%20of%20Donetsk.%3Cp%3EReuters%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20Carleton%20says%20that%20to%20retain%20the%20support%20of%20the%20public%2C%20Putin%20is%20more%20willing%20to%20dispatch%20certain%20Russians%20to%20the%20front%20lines%20than%20others.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20war%20is%20being%20fought%20and%20bled%20by%20the%20marginalized%20communities%20socioeconomically%20speaking%20%E2%80%94%20and%20very%20often%20racially%20and%20ethnically%2C%26quot%3B%20Carleton%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20Putin%20recruiting%20soldiers%20from%20villages%20in%20remote%20parts%20of%20Russia%20and%20among%20its%20non-Russian%20ethnic%20groups%2C%20Putin%20can%20avoid%20the%20perception%20of%20high%20casualty%20rates.%20Carleton%20cited%20estimates%20that%20for%20every%20soldier%20from%20Moscow%20who%20is%20killed%2C%20%26quot%3Banother%20couple%20of%20hundred%20have%20died%20already%20in%20these%20villages.%26quot%3B%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20deaths%20are%20being%20spread%20across%20the%20country%2C%26quot%3B%20Carleton%20said%2C%3Cstrong%3E%20%26quot%3B%3C%2Fstrong%3Ebut%20away%20from%20the%20major%20urban%20centers%2C%20because%20the%20major%20urban%20centers%20are%20where%20knowledge%20is%20disseminated%2C%26quot%3B%20Carleton%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20pupils%20in%20Russian%20schools%20are%20being%20prepared%20to%20embrace%20self-sacrifice%20by%20Putin's%20government%2C%20according%20to%20Barbieri%2C%20who%20described%20Soviet-style%20patriotic%20indoctrination%20programs%20tha