th%3D%5C%221024%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Glenn%20Youngkin%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F653985a896f7540cd06605b1%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22683%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EGov.%20Glenn%20Youngkin%20is%20firmly%20supportive%20of%20a%2015-week%20abortion%20ban%20in%20Virginia.%3Cp%3EAP%20Photo%2FStephanie%20Scarbrough%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%20%3Cli%3EVirginia%20is%20a%20critical%20Southern%20battleground%20in%20the%20fight%20over%20abortion%20policy%20ahead%20of%202024.%3C%2Fli%3E%20%3Cli%3ERepublican%20Gov.%20Glenn%20Youngkin%20wants%20to%20enact%20a%2015-week%20abortion%20ban%2C%20calling%20it%20%26quot%3Breasonable.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fli%3E%20%3Cli%3EDemocrats%20are%20pushing%20back%2C%20arguing%20that%20such%20a%20ban%20is%20a%20slippery%20slope%20to%20more%20restrictions.%3C%2Fli%3E%20%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20Virginia%2C%20there's%20little%20dispute%20that%20abortion%20is%20on%20the%20ballot.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20November%20legislative%20races%20in%20the%20Commonwealth%20are%20the%20first%20election%20cycle%20since%20last%20year's%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsupreme-court-abortion-decision-final-ruling-scotus-roe-v-wade-2022-6%5C%22%3Eoverturn%20of%20Roe%20v.%20Wade%3C%2Fa%3E%20where%20every%20seat%20in%20both%20chambers%20%E2%80%94%20100%20seats%20in%20the%20state%20House%20of%20Delegates%20and%2040%20seats%20in%20the%20state%20Senate%20%E2%80%94%20are%20up%20for%20grabs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDemocrats%20in%20the%20Commonwealth%20had%20been%20ascendant%20for%20much%20of%20the%20past%20decade%2C%20but%20they%20now%20have%20a%20major%20roadblock%20in%20Republican%20Gov.%20Glenn%20Youngkin%2C%20who%20turned%20out%20conservatives%20and%20flipped%20just%20enough%20swing%20voters%20in%202021%20to%20win%20that%20year's%20gubernatorial%20election.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20November%20elections%20have%20already%20scrambled%20Virginia's%20political%20calculus%2C%20as%20candidates%20across%20the%20Commonwealth%20are%20running%20in%20new%20legislative%20districts%20that%20resulted%20from%20the%20state's%20new%20redistricting%20process.%20A%20slew%20of%20veteran%20lawmakers%20opted%20out%20of%20running%20for%20reelection%20this%20year%2C%20which%20is%20poised%20to%20inject%20fresh%20blood%20into%20a%20legislature%20known%20for%20its%20collegiality%20and%20stability.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHere's%20how%20the%20explosive%20abortion%20debate%20is%20impacting%20races%20across%20Virginia%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3ERepublicans%20want%20a%20governing%20trifecta%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20Youngkin%20won%20the%20governorship%2C%20he%20brought%20along%20now-Lt.%20Gov.%20Winsome%20Sears%20and%20now-Attorney%20General%20Jason%20Miyares%20in%20a%20GOP%20sweep%20that%20put%20Democrats%20on%20notice%20that%20Virginia%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fvirginia-governor-race-terry-mcauliffe-glenn-youngkin-biden-democrats-trump-2021-10%5C%22%3Estill%20had%20a%20purplish%20tinge%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20House%20of%20Delegates%20flipping%20from%20Democratic%20control%20to%20the%20GOP%20that%20year%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fvirginia-house-of-delegates-elections-live-results-updates-2021-11%5C%22%3Efurther%20bolstered%3C%2Fa%3E%20this%20fact.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDemocrats%20still%20have%20a%20lot%20going%20for%20them%3A%20They%20have%20won%20every%20presidential%20election%20in%20Virginia%20since%20Barack%20Obama%20carried%20the%20state%20in%202008.%20Their%20strength%20in%20Northern%20Virginia%20and%20Hampton%20Roads%20%E2%80%94%20and%20increasingly%20in%20Richmond's%20suburbs%20%E2%80%94%20has%20often%20allowed%20them%20to%20offset%20the%20rural%20strength%20that%20Republicans%20enjoy.%20And%20most%20Virginia%20voters%20back%20some%20form%20of%20abortion%20rights%2C%20with%20a%20recent%20Washington%20Post-Schar%20School%20poll%20revealing%20that%2051%25%20of%20likely%20voters%20think%20Democrats%20are%20better