nsider.com%2Fus-plans-first-fusion-plant-for-pollution-free-energy-2023-9%5C%22%3Efusion%20power%20plants%3C%2Fa%3E%20are%20possible.%3C%2Fli%3E%20%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EOver%20the%20past%20year%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsecond-nuclear-fusion-reaction-experiment-yields-more-energy-2023-8%5C%22%3Enuclear%20fusion%20experiments%3C%2Fa%3E%20at%20the%20National%20Ignition%20Facility%20achieved%20a%20huge%20milestone%20when%20their%20reactions%20yielded%20more%20energy%20than%20they%20put%20into%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20feats%20are%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhat-is-nuclear-fusion-how-does-it-work-green-energy-breakthrough%5C%22%3Emonumental%20first%20for%20fusion%20physics%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20bring%20humanity%20one%20step%20closer%20to%20harnessing%20the%20same%20type%20of%20colossal%20energy%20that%20powers%20our%20sun.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20the%20NIF%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Faffiliate.insider.com%3Fh%3D4fd3ae11dd8699a30b399f6df78333ceb2cab81e84484fddbd533c84330eb2a5%26postID%3D65317d56e20e2d7dddaa6736%26postSlug%3Dwhy-no-fusion-energy-power-plants-yet-how-2023-10%26site%3Dbi%26u%3Dhttps%253A%252F%252Fwww.nature.com%252Farticles%252Fd41586-022-04440-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eisn't%20focusing%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20commercial%20applications%2C%20its%20scientific%20breakthrough%20lays%20the%20groundwork%20for%20a%20slew%20of%20research%20institutions%20and%20startups%20that%20are%20pouring%20hundreds%20of%20millions%20of%20dollars%20into%20building%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhelion-energy-fusion-company-backed-by-sam-altman-and-microsoft-2023-5%5C%22%3Efirst%20fusion%20power%20plants%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Some%20have%20ambitious%20goals%2C%20saying%20they'll%20bring%20electricity%20to%20homes%20as%20soon%20as%202028.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFusion%20plants%20could%20theoretically%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.iaea.org%2Fnewscenter%2Fnews%2Fwhat-is-nuclear-fusion%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eproduce%3C%2Fa%3E%20almost%204%20million%20times%20as%20much%20energy%20as%20burning%20coal%20or%20oil%20%E2%80%94%20with%20none%20of%20the%20carbon%20emissions.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20first%2C%20researchers%20need%20to%20reliably%20create%20a%20burning%20plasma%20%E2%80%94%20a%20self-heating%20mix%20of%20atomic%20nuclei%20and%20free%20electrons%20%E2%80%94%20that%20outputs%20more%20energy%20than%20it%20takes%20to%20fuel%20the%20reaction.%20It's%20what%20Andrew%20Christlieb%2C%20who%20is%20part%20of%20a%20US%20Department%20of%20Energy%20fusion%20project%20at%20Michigan%20State%20University%2C%20calls%20%26quot%3Bstep%20zero.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThen%20you%20get%20into%20a%20whole%20bunch%20of%20engineering%20questions%26quot%3B%20that%20he%20predicts%20will%20take%20at%20least%2020%20years%20to%20solve.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESo%20the%20prospect%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmicrosoft-helion-energy-nuclear-fusion-power-plant-2023-5%5C%22%3Efusion%20plants%20powering%20US%20cities%20by%202028%3C%2Fa%3E%20might%20be%20too%20ambitious%20for%20hungry-eyed%20investors%20intent%20on%20ushering%20in%20a%20new%20age%20of%20clean%20energy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EHurdle%201%3A%20It%20takes%20a%20ton%20of%20energy%20to%20harness%20the%20power%20of%20the%20sun%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAlmost%2090%20years%20ago%2C%20scientists%20first%20discovered%20how%20to%20produce%20energy%20from%20fusion.%20Fusion%20occurs%20when%20multiple%20atoms%20bind%2C%20or%20fuse%2C%20together%20to%20form%20new%20atoms.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20process%2C%20%26quot%3Ba%20little%20bit%20of%20mass%20gets%20converted%20into%20energy%2C%20but%20that%20little%20bit%20of%20mass%20gets%20converted%20into%20a%20lot%20of%20energy%2C%26quot%3B%20Christlieb%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221998%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Inside%20the%20circular%20structure%20of%20the%20NSTX-U%20at%20the%20PPPL%2C%20with%20many%20pieces%20of%20metal%20in%20different%20colors%20protruding%20into%20the%20interior.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F653183c596908fd7cdb2f96b%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221498%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20look%20inside%20the%20NSTX-U%20at%20the%20PPPL.%3Cp%3EMichael%20Livingston%2C%20PPPL%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwe-will-never-have-sun-like-nuclear-fusion-2014-10%5C%22%3Esun%20achieves%20nuclear%20fusion%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20its%20core%2C%20where%20temperatures%20are%2027%20million%20degrees%20Fahrenheit%2C%20and%20the%20pressure%20is%20100%20billion%20times%20that%20of%20Earth's%20atmosphere.%20Reproducing%20those%20conditions%20on%20Earth%20to%20harness%20that%20power%20is%20a%20technological%20challenge%2C%20to%20say%20the%20least.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThree%20scientists%20first%20achieved%20such%20a%20feat%20in%20the%20lab%20in%201934%2C%20when%20they%20bombarded%20a%20type%20of%20hydrogen%20atom%20with%20another%20type%20of%20subatomic%20particle%20called%20a%20deuteron.%20The%20results%20produced%20%26quot%3Ban%20enormous%20effect%2C%26quot%3B%20they%20reported%20in%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Froyalsocietypublishing.org%2Fdoi%2F10.1098%2Frspa.1934.0077%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EThe%20Proceedings%20of%20the%20Royal%20Society%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20sustaining%20a%20fusion%20experiment%20to%20generate%20continuous%20streams%20of%20energy%20is%20what%20scientists%20have%20been%20chasing%20ever%20since.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20three%20ways%20scientists%20control%20fusion%20reactions%20on%20Earth%20today%3A%20by%20forcing%20a%20capsule%20of%20fuel%20to%20implode%2C%20by%20using%20magnetic%20fields%20to%20confine%20plasma%2C%20or%20by%20combining%20the%20two%20methods.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20fusion%20experiments%20at%20NIF%20use%20lasers%20for%20the%20implosion%20method.%20But%20the%20amount%20of%20energy%20needed%20to%20power%20the%20lasers%20has%20typically%20exceeded%20the%20energy%20the%20fusion%20reaction%20produces.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221422%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22The%20MUSE%20device%20at%20the%20PPPL%2C%20with%20a%20window%20showing%20a%20glowing%20red%20interior%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F653182f596f7540cd060d50f%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221066%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EMUSE%2C%20a%20tabletop%20model%20under%20development%20at%20PPPL%2C%20which%20creates%20magnetic%20fields%20to%20control%20plasma.%3Cp%3EMichael%20Livingston%2C%20PPPL%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EHurdle%202%3A%20Tritium%20is%20rare%20and%20expensive%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20get%20the%20molecules%20hot%20enough%20to%20slam%20into%20each%20other%20and%20fuse%2C%20researchers%20form%20a%20plasma.%20It's%20a%20slurry%20of%20two%20hydrogen%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Foppenheimer-science-to-understand-physics-atomic-bombs-2023-7%5C%22%3Eisotopes%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20deuterium%20and%20tritium.%20Only%20a%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.iter.org%2Fsci%2FFusionFuels%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efew%20grams%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20each%20are%20needed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20deuterium%20is%20plentiful%2C%20tritium%20is%20exceedingly%20rare%2C%20costing%20as%20much%20as%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.science.org%2Fcontent%2Farticle%2Ffusion-power-may-run-fuel-even-gets-started%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%2430%2C000%20per%20gram%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20current%20stockpile%20consists%20of%20only%20about%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.science.org%2Fcontent%2Farticle%2Ffusion-power-may-run-fuel-even-gets-started%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E55%20pounds%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Researchers%20hope%20to%20make%20fusion%20reactors%20that%20create%20their%20own%20supply%20of%20tritium.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBreeder%20blankets%20are%20one%20option.%20The%20high-energy%20neutrons%20coming%20off%20of%20the%20fusion%20reactions%20would%20hit%20the%20surrounding%20%26quot%3Bblanket%26quot%3B%20of%20lithium%20and%20split%20it%20into%20helium%20and%20tritium.%20The%20tritium%20could%20then%20be%20collected%20and%20fed%20back%20into%20the%20reactor.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20large%20circular%20metal%20structure%20under%20construction%20at%20ITER%20in%20France%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F653c1b87356802a56be68f7d%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221500%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20circular%20bioshield%20under%20construction%20at%20the%20International%20Thermonuclear%20Experimental%20Reactor%20(ITER)%20in%20Saint-Paul-lez-Durance%2C%20Southern%20France%20in%202018.%3Cp%3EREUTERS%2FJean-Paul%20Pelissier%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20get%20up%20and%20running%2C%20large%20reactors%20like%20the%20International%20Thermonuclear%20Experimental%20Reactor%20need%20several%20pounds%20of%20tritium%20each.%20The%20world's%20largest%20fusion%20project%2C%20ITER%20might%20not%20get%20up%20and%20running%20until%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.scientificamerican.com%2Farticle%2Fwhat-is-the-future-of-fusion-energy%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E2040s%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20it's%20being%20used%20for%20research%20instead%20of%20commercial%20purposes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20of%20ITER's%20main%20goals%20is%20to%20produce%20a%20burning%20plasma.%20An%20international%20collaboration%20between%20the%20European%20Union%2C%20the%20US%2C%20China%2C%20Russia%2C%20and%20other%20countries%2C%20it's%20also%20way%20over%20budget.%20Originally%20expected%20to%20be%20up%20and%20running%20by%202016%20for%20around%20%246.3%20billion%2C%20it's%20now%20several%20years%20behind%20and%20over%20three%20times%20the%20original%20cost%20estimate%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.scientificamerican.com%2Farticle%2Fworlds-largest-fusion-project-is-in-big-trouble-new-documents-reveal%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EScientific%20American%3C%2Fa%3E%20reported.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EHurdle%203%3A%20Containing%20something%20hotter%20than%20the%20sun%20is%20difficult%3Cbr%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ECreating%20a%20magnetic%20containment%20device%20to%20hold%20plasma%20is%20its%20own%20challenge.%20Plasma%20needs%20to%20reach%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.iter.org%2Fmag%2F2%2F18%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etemperatures%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20150%20million%20degrees%20Celsius%20and%20above.%20That's%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhat-if-humans-tried-landing-sun-2020-2%5C%22%3Ehotter%20than%20the%20sun%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEven%20the%20most%20heat-resistant%20metal%20container%20can't%20hold%20the%20plasma.%20Any%20material%20would%20get%20damaged.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224444%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20a%20gold-plated%20hohlraum%20from%20the%20National%20Ignition%20Facility%20glows%20green%20against%20a%20black%20background%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F653183e296f7540cd060d724%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223333%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20National%20Ignition%20Facility's%20192%20laser%20beams%20are%20aimed%20at%20a%20hohlraum%2C%20which%20holds%20the%20deuterium%20and%20tritium%20capsule.%3Cp%3EJason%20Laurea%2FLawrence%20Livermore%20National%20Laboratory%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20of%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.iaea.org%2Fnewscenter%2Fnews%2Ftokamaks-stellarators-laser-based-and-alternative-concepts-report-offers-global-perspective-on-nuclear-fusion-devices%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emost%20common%3C%2Fa%3E%20plasma-confinement%20solutions%20is%20a%20tokamak.%20The%20device%20functions%20as%20a%20kind%20of%20%26quot%3Bmagnetic%20bottle.%26quot%3B%20The%20plasma%20particles%20follow%20the%20invisible%20lines%20of%20the%20magnetic%20field%20and%20don't%20stray%20beyond.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EHurdle%204%3A%20It's%20a%20finicky%20reaction%20%3Cbr%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EA%20metal%20plasma-containment%20device%20would%20also%20cool%20the%20contents%20and%20stop%20the%20fusion%20process.%20That's%20one%20reason%20fusion%20reactors%20can't%20have%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchernobyl-nuclear-disaster-strange-events-afterwards-2019-7%5C%22%3EChernobyl-like%20meltdowns%3C%2Fa%3E.%20It's%20such%20a%20finicky%20reaction%20that%20disturbances%20cause%20it%20to%20cool%20down%20and%20stop.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPlus%2C%20plasma%20can%20behave%20weirdly.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20like%20when%20you're%20squeezing%20Jell-O%20in%20your%20hand%2C%26quot%3B%20Christlieb%20said.%20%26quot%3BIt%20finds%20these%20little%20holes%20to%20squeeze%20out%20of%20because%20your%20hand%20isn't%20perfectly%20sealed.%26quot%3B%20The%20tokamak%20has%20to%20be%20able%20to%20adapt%20to%20the%20changes%20in%20the%20plasma.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20the%20plasma%20changes%20its%20behavior%2C%20it%20can%20interact%20with%20and%20damage%20the%20wall%20of%20the%20device.%20The%20Princeton%20lab%20is%20experimenting%20with%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.pppl.gov%2Fresearch%2Fprojects%2Flithium-tokamak-experiment%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eliquid%20metal%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20some%20fusion%20reactor%20components.%20Jonathan%20Menard%2C%20chief%20research%20officer%20at%20the%20Princeton%20Plasma%20Physics%20Laboratory%2C%20compares%20it%20to%20the%20T-1000%20in%20%26quot%3BTerminator%202%2C%26quot%3B%20making%20it%20almost%20self-repairing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EHurdle%205%3A%20Tritium%20is%20still%20radioactive%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThough%20tritium%20has%20a%20much%20shorter%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nrc.gov%2Freading-rm%2Fdoc-collections%2Ffact-sheets%2Fradwaste.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehalf-life%3C%2Fa%3E%20than%20Plutonium-239%20(12.3%20years%20compared%20to%2024%2C000%20years)%2C%20the%20former%20has%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcen.acs.org%2Farticles%2F84%2Fi26%2FRadioactive-Leaks-Found-Reactors.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebeen%20known%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20leak%20into%20groundwater%20from%20nuclear%20power%20plants.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBecause%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhelion-energy-fusion-company-backed-by-sam-altman-and-microsoft-2023-5%5C%22%3Efusion%20power%20plants%3C%2Fa%3E%20would%20be%20a%20brand%20new%20type%20of%20facility%2C%20there%20are%20still%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmarkets.businessinsider.com%2Fnews%2Fstocks%2Fnuclear-fusion-a-clean-energy-revolution-or-a-radioactive-nightmare-1032400280%5C%22%3Ea%20lot%20of%20unknowns%3C%2Fa%3E%20when%20it%20comes%20to%20other%20safety%20concerns.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20recent%20report%20looked%20at%20everything%20from%20earthquakes%20to%20fires%20to%20terror%20attacks.%20Some%20scenarios%2C%20like%20electromagnetic%20discharge%20%E2%80%94%20where%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.sciencedirect.com%2Fscience%2Farticle%2Fabs%2Fpii%2FS0920379619308737%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emagnet%20systems%20fail%20and%20cause%20the%20energy%20to%20arc%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20and%20accidents%20involving%20breeder%20blankets%20need%20further%20study%2C%20the%20authors%20warned.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EExperts%20think%20it'll%20take%20decades%20for%20commercial%20fusion%20power%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EDespite%20the%20large%20number%20of%20challenges%2C%20both%20Menard%20and%20Christlieb%20were%20optimistic%20about%20the%20future%20of%20fusion%20power.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20it's%20still%20some%20way%20off.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20not%20single%20digits%2C%26quot%3B%20Menard%20said.%20It's%20decades.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20perennial%20joke%20about%20fusion%20is%20it's%20always%2010%20years%20away%2C%26quot%3B%20Christlieb%20said.%20But%20he%20does%20think%20it's%20closer%20than%20ever%20before.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20US%20government%20has%20invested%20in%20fusion%20energy%20since%20the%201950s.%20The%20US%20Department%20of%20Energy's%20Fusion%20Energy%20Sciences%20program%20has%20a%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcrsreports.congress.gov%2Fproduct%2Fpdf%2FIF%2FIF12411%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%24763%20million%3C%2Fa%3E%20budget%20for%202023%2C%20which%20could%20grow%20to%20over%20%241%20billion%20next%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.fusionindustryassociation.org%2Ffusion-industry-reports%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EFusion%20Industry%20Association%3C%2Fa%3E%20puts%20overall%20fusion%20investment%20at%20around%20%246%20billion.%20Tech%20moguls%20like%20Bill%20Gates%20and%20Sam%20Altman%20are%20pouring%20money%20into%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmicrosoft-helion-first-ever-deal-for-fusion-energy-by-2028-2023-5%5C%22%3Efusion%20projects%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAchieving%20commercial%20fusion%20power%20in%20two%20decades%20won't%20be%20quick%20enough%20to%20address%20many%20countries'%20goals%20of%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fglobal-warming-point-of-no-return-temperature-2018-8%5C%22%3E%20adapting%20clean%20energy%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fclimate-ipcc-report-temperature-rise-20-years-15-degrees-2021-