20towns%20adjoining%20the%20Nepal%20border%2C%20they%20still%20come%20over%20for%20employment%20as%20casual%20labour%2C%20and%20it%20is%20this%20group%20of%20men%20that%20Diwa%20Shah%20has%20empathetically%20captured%20in%20her%20debut%20feature%C2%A0%3Cem%3EBahadur%20The%20Brave%3C%2Fem%3E.%20Set%20in%20Naintal%20during%20the%20pandemic%2C%20the%20film%20tells%20the%20story%20of%20two%20Nepali%20friends%2C%20who%20have%20to%20make%20tough%20decisions%20about%20their%20future.%20The%20film%20won%20Shah%20the%20Kutxabank%20New%20Director%E2%80%99s%20Award%20at%20the%20San%20Sebastian%20Film%20Festival%20in%20Spain%20%E2%80%93%20a%20first%20for%20an%20Indian%20film%20%E2%80%93%20and%20is%20in%20competition%20at%20the%20ongoing%20Jio%20MAMI%20Film%20Festival.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20film%20follows%20the%20somewhat%20simple-minded%20Hansi%20(Rupesh%20Lama)%2C%20who%20does%20odd%20jobs%20of%20fetching%20and%20carrying%20loads%20like%20sacks%20of%20grain%20and%20gas%20cylinders%20for%20the%20neighbouring%20shopkeepers%20and%20homemakers.%20When%20the%20coronavirus%20strikes%20and%20a%20strict%20lockdown%20is%20imposed%20in%20the%20hill%20town%2C%20Hansi%20finds%20ways%20of%20dodging%20the%20curfew%2C%20and%20it%20hurts%20when%20he%20is%20fined%20Rs%20500%20by%20the%20cops%20for%20not%20wearing%20a%20mask%20%E2%80%93%20money%20he%20has%20just%20scraped%20together%20by%20haggling%20with%20his%20employers.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EHansi%E2%80%99s%20buddy%20and%20brother-in-law%2C%20Dil%20Bahadur%20(Rahul%20Mukhia)%2C%20takes%20advantage%20of%20the%20shortage%20of%20labour%20by%20accepting%20construction%20jobs.%20The%20lockdown%20is%20tough%20on%20them%20as%20their%20roommates%20start%20going%20back%20to%20Nepal%20one%20by%20one%2C%20and%20the%20few%20that%20remain%20are%20forced%20to%20stay%20indoors%2C%20playing%20cards%20and%20taking%20turns%20cooking%20meals.%20Their%20already%20hard-scrabble%20existence%20is%20made%20more%20difficult%20by%20unexpectedly%20cruel%20circumstances.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EHansi%20gets%20news%20that%20his%20son%20who%20needs%20surgery%20for%20a%20stomach%20ailment%20has%20fallen%20down%20and%20broken%20his%20arm.%20But%20he%20is%20ashamed%20to%20go%20home%20without%20money.%20Every%20time%20Dil%20Bahadur%20makes%20arrangements%20for%20him%20to%20return%2C%C2%A0%20Hansi%20finds%20excuses%20to%20miss%20the%20bus.%20For%20a%20man%20who%20has%20trouble%20following%20basic%20conversations%20(his%20interactions%20with%20a%20kind%20housewife%20are%20hilarious)%2C%20Hansi%20also%20has%20hidden%20reserves%20of%20sly%20resourcefulness%20%E2%80%93%20like%20persuading%20a%20cop%20to%20lie%20to%20Dil%20Bahadur%20about%20the%20expiry%20of%20his%20travel%20permit%20so%20that%20he%20can%20avoid%20getting%20on%20the%20bus%20to%20Nepal.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20impasse%20is%20automatically%20broken%20when%20Hansi%20and%20Dil%20Bahadur%20steal%20some%20liquor%20from%20a%20warehouse%20and%20are%20caught%20on%20the%20CCTV%20camera.%20The%20boss%20accuses%20Dil%20Bahadur%20of%20also%20stealing%20money%20and%20threatens%20to%20call%20the%20cops.%C2%A0Hansi%20uses%20this%20incident%20to%20persuade%20Dil%20Bahadur%20to%20go%20back%2C%20promising%20to%20follow.%20Inadvertently%2C%20this%20innocent%20ploy%20results%20in%20tragedy.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EMemories%20of%20lockdown%20coverage%20in%20print%20and%20TV%20enumerated%20the%20deaths%20of%20Indian%20migrant%20workers%20trying%20desperately%20to%20reach%20their%20families.%20Poor%20Nepali%20migrants%2C%20who%20were%20not%20even%20citizens%20of%20India%2C%20were%20trapped%20when%20the%20border%20was%20sealed.%20Hostile%20locals%20shouted%20slogans%20to%20exhort%20the%20Nepal%20government%20to%20take%20their%20citizens%20back.%20The%20migrants%20had%20to%20camp%20out%20in%20the%20cold%20at%20the%20border%2C%20with%20no%20money%20and%20no%20access%20to%20food%20or%20supplies.%20The%20governments%20on%20either%20side%20couldn%E2%80%99t%20care%20less%20about%20these%20powerless%20men%2C%20who%20had%20nothing%20to%20offer%20in%20return%20for%20safe%20passage.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EDiwa%20Shah%E2%80%99s%20treatment%20of%20the%20subject%20is%20understated%20but%20also%20deeply%20humane.%20She%20portrays%20the%20bleakness%20of%20the%20lives%20of%20these%20migrants%20against%20a%20backdrop%20of%20scenic%20beauty.%20There%20is%20some%20humour%20and%20joy%20even%20in%20a%20crisis%20when%20the%20group%20of%20workers%20get%20together.%20But%20a%20desperate%20Hansi%20is%20left%20to%20stew%20in%20guilt%20and%20helplessness.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EBoth%20the%20lead%20actors%20bring%20out%20the%20truth%20and%20realism%20of%20the%20story%20with%20their%20performances%3B%20the%20viewer%20cannot%20but%20sympathise%20with%20the%20plight%20of%20these%20Bahadurs%20trying%20to%20keep%20their%20families%20out%20of%20abject%20poverty.%20The%20film%20is%20a%20reminder%20that%20the%20famed%20resilience%20of%20the%20poor%20comes%20at%20a%20steep%20price.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EDeepa%20Gahlot%20is%20a%20national%20award%20winning%20critic%20and%20columnist.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1698578731000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F29164548%2FBahadur-the-Brave-2023_02-768x417-1.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Ffilm%2Fbahadur-the-brave-shows-how-for-nepalese-migrant-workers-the-lockdown-was-even-more-difficult%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Debutante%20director%20Diwa%20Shah%E2%80%99s%20award-winning%20film%20showing%20at%20the%20Jio-MAMI%20festival%20is%20a%20sensitive%20look%20at%20their%20travails.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A1%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Ffilm%2Fbahadur-the-brave-shows-how-for-nepalese-migrant-workers-the-lockdown-was-even-more-difficult%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22A%20third%20of%20Columbus%2C%20Ohio's%20population%20just%20had%20%24335%20million%20in%20medical%20debt%20wiped%20out%20thanks%20to%20Biden's%20American%20Rescue%20Plan%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%225616%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22The%20exterior%20of%20Columbus%20City%20Hall.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F653d3b2b356802a56be6ccb5%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223744%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EColumbus%2C%20Ohio%20has%20launched%20a%20program%20to%20forgive%20%24335%20million%20in%20medical%20debt%20for%20their%20residents.%3Cp%3ERaymond%20Boyd%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EOhio's%20capital%20is%20forgiving%20%24335%20million%20in%20medical%20debt.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EBiden's%20American%20Rescue%20Plan%20funded%20the%20forgiveness%20program.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20city%20will%20only%20pay%20%24500%2C000%20to%20reimburse%20hospitals%20for%20administrative%20work.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EOver%20the%20last%20two%20weeks%2C%20four%20hospital%20systems%20in%20Columbus%2C%20Ohio%20began%20sending%20hundreds%20of%20thousands%20of%20letters%20to%20residents%20across%20the%20city.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20one%20letter%20they'll%20be%20glad%20to%20open.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20letters%20are%20informing%20more%20than%20300%2C000%20residents%20that%20some%2C%20if%20not%20all%2C%20of%20their%20medical%20debt%20will%20be%20forgiven.%20All%20told%2C%20the%20hospitals%20are%20wiping%20clean%20about%20%24335%20million%20in%20medical%20debt%20for%20nearly%20one-third%20of%20the%20city's%20population.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20relief%20comes%20thanks%20to%20funds%20from%20President%20Joe%20Biden's%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-towns-states-use-pandemic-stimulus-cash-guaranteed-basic-income-2023-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAmerican%20Rescue%20Plan%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20a%20%241.9%20trillion%20economic%20package%20launched%20in%20March%202021%20that%20was%20designed%20to%20jump-start%20the%20economy%20amid%20the%20COVID-19%20pandemic.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20program%20is%20only%20costing%20the%20city%20%24500%2C000%2C%20which%20will%20go%20toward%20reimbursing%20the%20hospital%20systems%20for%20sending%20the%20letters%20and%20other%20administrative%20tasks.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Columbus%20City%20Council%20first%20approved%20the%20plan%20on%20October%2016%20after%20months%20of%20research%20and%20planning.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20proposed%20legislation%20initially%20outlined%20a%20%24200%20million%20forgiveness%20program%20that%20would've%20cost%20the%20city%20%242%20million%2C%20City%20Council%20President%20Pro%20Tem%20Rob%20Dorans%20told%20Insider.%20The%20plan%20was%20made%20together%20with%20the%20Central%20Ohio%20Hospital%20Council%2C%20which%20represents%20four%20major%20hospital%20systems%20in%20the%20region.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EInitially%2C%20the%20city%20planned%20to%20partner%20with%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frip-medical-debt-wipes-out-278-million-medical-debt-wsj-2021-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ERIP%20Medical%20Debt%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20nonprofit%20based%20in%20New%20York.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BRIP%20Medical%20Debt%20was%20very%20generous%20with%20their%20time%2C%20and%20they%20do%20excellent%20work%2C%26quot%3B%20Dorans%20told%20Insider.%20%26quot%3BHowever%2C%20we%20started%20having%20direct%20conversations%20with%20the%20four%20hospital%20systems%20in%20central%20Ohio%2C%20and%20they%20kept%20coming%20to%20us%2C%20saying%20there%20may%20not%20be%20a%20need%20to%20have%20a%20third%20party%20be%20engaged%20on%20this.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOther%20cities%20in%20Ohio%20have%20launched%20similar%20programs.%20In%20Toledo%2C%2041%2C000%20residents%20saw%20%24240%20million%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftoledo-ohio-medical-debt-relief-with-biden-funds-2023-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emedical%20debt%20relief%3C%2Fa%3E%20last%20month%2C%20Insider%20previously%20reported.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMedical%20debt%20is%20the%20leading%20cause%20of%20personal%20bankruptcy%20in%20the%20United%20States%2C%20according%20to%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fapnews.com%2Farticle%2Fmedical-debt-legislation-2a4f2fab7e2c58a68ac4541b8309c7aa%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAssociated%20Press%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20address%20this%20nationwide%20issue%2C%20several%20counties%20and%20cities%20outside%20Ohio%20are%20using%20their%20American%20Rescue%20Plan%20funds%20to%20forgive%20medical%20debt%20as%20well.%20Cook%20County%2C%20Illinois%2C%20New%20Orleans%2C%20Louisiana%2C%20and%20Pittsburgh%2C%20Pennsylvania%2C%20have%20all%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.whitehouse.gov%2Fbriefing-room%2Fstatements-releases%2F2023%2F02%2F14%2Ffact-sheet-new-data-show-8-2-million-fewer-americans-struggling-with-medical-debt-under-the-biden-harris-administration%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eimplemented%20similar%20plans%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20provide%20medical%20debt%20relief.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJeff%20Klingler%2C%20president%20and%20CEO%20of%20the%20Central%20Ohio%20Hospital%20Council%2C%20said%20he%20hopes%20Columbus'%20model%20will%20inspire%20other%20cities%20and%20hospital%20systems%20to%20adopt%20similar%20programs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI'm%20kind%20of%20hoping%20that%20my%20counterparts%20around%20the%20country%2C%20maybe%20they'll%20reach%20out%20to%20us%20and%20find%20out%20how%20we%20did%20it%2C%26quot%3B%20Klingler%20told%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EColumbus%20is%20providing%20relief%20based%20on%20income%20and%20residence%20within%20city%20limits%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20qualify%20for%20relief%2C%20patients%20must%20have%20received%20treatment%20at%20one%20of%20the%20four%20hospital%20systems%20in%20the%20region%20represented%20by%20the%20Central%20Ohio%20Hospital%20Council%20and%20reside%20within%20Columbus%20city%20limits.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPatients%20must%20also%20have%20an%20income%20between%20200%25%20and%20400%25%20of%20the%20federal%20poverty%20level%2C%20according%20to%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fnew.columbus.gov%2FNews-articles%2FCity-Leaders-Announce-335-Million-in-Medical-Debt-Relief%23%3A~%3Atext%3DToday%2520Council%2520President%2520Shannon%2520Hardin%2Cmedical%2520debt%2520for%2520Columbus%2520residents.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Estatement%3C%2Fa%3E%20from%20the%20Columbus%20City%20Council.%20That's%20between%20%2455%2C500%20and%20%24111%2C000%20for%20a%20family%20of%20four.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnyone%20who%20makes%20less%20than%20200%25%20of%20the%20federal%20poverty%20level%20already%20qualifies%20to%20receive%20medical%20care%20free%20of%20charge%2C%20the%20statement%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERelief%20does%20not%20apply%20to%20anyone%20living%20in%20the%20Columbus%20suburbs%20in%20the%20greater%20Franklin%20County%20region.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20Andrea%2C%20a%20Franklin%20County%20resident%20whose%20last%20name%20is%20known%20to%20Insider%20but%20withheld%20due%20to%20privacy%20concerns%2C%20the%20relief%20program%20offered%20hope%20until%20she%20realized%20it%20wouldn't%20apply%20to%20her%20because%20she%20doesn't%20live%20within%20city%20limits.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAndrea%20told%20Insider%20she%20has%20%244%2C029.25%20in%20medical%20debt%20after%20giving%20birth%20at%20Ohio%20State%20University%2C%20one%20of%20the%20hospitals%20covered%20in%20the%20relief%20plan.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20was%20hoping%20that%20it%20was%20going%20to%20be%20forgiven%2C%26quot%3B%20Andrea%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAndrea%20gave%20birth%20just%20months%20before%20the%20COVID-19%20pandemic%20hit.%20Over%20the%20next%20year%2C%20her%20husband%20was%20laid%20off%2C%20and%20both%20of%20Andrea's%20parents%20died.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20whole%20world%20was%20crumbling%2C%26quot%3B%20Andrea%20said.%20%26quot%3BI%20was%20like%2C%20'Who%20gives%20a%20shit%20about%20medical%20bills%3F'%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAndrea's%20debt%20has%20now%20been%20sent%20to%20collections%2C%20and%20the%20state%