8-crore-project-from-nhai-123102900496_1.html%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Famp%2Fcompanies%2Fnews%2Firb-infrastructure-trust-gets-loa-for-rs-4-428-crore-project-from-nhai-123102900496_1.html%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Cold%20War%20US%20spy%20satellite%20images%20reveal%20nearly%20400%20undiscovered%20Roman%20forts%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221583%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Newly%20discovered%20Roman%20forts%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F653bd1cd356802a56be5e064%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221189%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ENewly%20discovered%20Roman%20forts.%3Cp%3EAntiquity%2FUS%20Geological%20Survey%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%20%3Cli%3ESatellite%20images%20taken%20during%20the%20Cold%20War%20have%20revealed%20almost%20400%20previously%20unknown%20Roman%20forts.%3C%2Fli%3E%20%3Cli%3EThe%20findings%20were%20published%20in%20Antiquity%2C%20an%20academic%20journal%20focusing%20on%20archaeology.%3C%2Fli%3E%20%3Cli%3EThey%20suggest%20that%20Rome's%20eastern%20frontier%20was%20a%20hub%20of%20trade%20rather%20than%20a%20defensive%20border.%3C%2Fli%3E%20%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3ESatellite%20images%20taken%20during%20the%20Cold%20War%20have%20revealed%20almost%20400%20previously%20undiscovered%20Roman%20forts%20across%20Iraq%20and%20Syria%2C%20archaeologists%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20research%2C%20published%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cambridge.org%2Fcore%2Fjournals%2Fantiquity%2Farticle%2Fwall-or-a-road-a-remote-sensingbased-investigation-of-fortifications-on-romes-eastern-frontier%2F8FE59FB0D5476EA329614EEC6DC414FD%5C%22%3EAntiquity%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20an%20academic%20journal%20that%20focuses%20on%20archaeology%2C%20has%20forced%20historians%20and%20archaeologists%20to%20re-evaluate%20their%20understanding%20of%20Rome's%20eastern%20front%2C%201%2C900%20years%20ago.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20area%20was%20previously%20surveyed%20by%20Antoine%20Poidebard%2C%20a%20French%20Jesuit%20priest%20who%20pioneered%20aerial%20archaeology%20in%20the%201920s.%20He%20mapped%20116%20Roman%20forts%20along%20a%201%2C000%20km%2C%20or%20roughly%20620-mile%2C%20border%2C%20suggesting%20that%20these%20represented%20a%20defensive%20line%20against%20Arab%20and%20Persian%20invaders%20due%20to%20their%20spacing.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221582%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Some%20of%20Poidebard's%20aerial%20photographs.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F653bd01b96f7540cd067a5d2%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221187%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ESome%20of%20Poidebard's%20aerial%20photographs.%3Cp%3EAntiquity%2FUS%20Geological%20Survey%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20new%20research%20found%20a%20further%20396%20previously%20undiscovered%20forts%2C%20suggesting%20that%20the%20region%20was%20more%20likely%20a%20hub%20of%20global%20trade.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20findings%20suggested%20that%20the%20forts%20were%20used%20to%20%26quot%3Bsupport%20movement%20of%20people%2C%20goods%2C%20and%20military%20assets%20between%20east%20and%20west%2C%26quot%3B%20Jesse%20Casana%2C%20the%20lead%20author%20of%20the%20study%20and%20a%20professor%20of%20anthropology%20at%20Dartmouth%20College%2C%20shared%20with%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECasana's%20team%20now%20has%20a%20simple%20question%3A%20was%20it%20%26quot%3Ba%20wall%20or%20a%20road%3F%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPrevious%20theories%20had%20imagined%20the%20forts%20as%20defining%20a%20north-south%20defensive%20border%2C%20but%20the%20newly%20discovered%20forts%20a%20showed%20an%20%26quot%3Beast-west%20trending%20line%20connecting%20the%20Tigris%20River%20with%20the%20Mediterranean%2C%26quot%3B%20Casana%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3ECold%20War%20imagery%C2%A0%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20photographs%20used%20in%20the%20study%20came%20from%20declassified%20spy%20images%20from%20the%20CORONA%20and%20HEXAGON%20satellite%20programs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECORONA%2C%20which%20started%20in%20the%20late%201950s%2C%20was%20designed%20to%20search%20images%20of%20the%20Earth's%20surface%20%26quot%3Bfor%20answers%20to%20the%20nation's%20pressing%20intelligence%20questions.%26quot%3B%20It%20became%20the%20%26quot%3Bsingle%20most%20important%20source%20of%20intelligence%20on%20Soviet%20strategic%20forces%2C%26quot%3B%20according%20to%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cia.gov%2Flegacy%2Fmuseum%2Fexhibit%2Fcorona-americas-first-imaging-satellite-program%2F%5C%22%3ECIA%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223769%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22The%20HEXAGON%20satellite%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F653bd4e696f7540cd067ae6d%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222827%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20HEXAGON%20satellite.%3Cp%3EPAUL%20J.%20RICHARDS%2FAFP%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EHEXAGON%20saw%20the%20%26quot%3Blargest%20and%20last%26quot%3B%20US%20intelligence%20satellites%20bring%20photographic%20film%20back%20to%20earth%2C%20capturing%20%26quot%3B877%20million%20square%20miles%20of%20the%20Earth's%20surface%20between%201971-1986%2C%26quot%3B%20per%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nationalmuseum.af.mil%2FVisit%2FMuseum-Exhibits%2FFact-Sheets%2FDisplay%2FArticle%2F195921%2Fhexagon-kh-9-reconnaissance-satellite%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ENational%20Museum%20of%20the%20United%20States%20Air%20Force%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Analysts%20used%20the%20images%20to%20identify%20potential%20threats.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECasana%20said%20the%20%26quot%3Bnext%20steps%20should%20be%20to%20expand%20this%20kind%20of%20research%20both%20to%20other%20regions%20of%20the%20world%2C%20as%20well%20as%20using%20additional%20types%20of%20imagery.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcold-war-us-spy-satellite