tening%20the%20world's%20second%20largest%20economy's%20financial%20stability.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20top%20of%20that%2C%20China%20can't%20seem%20to%20get%20its%20young%20college%20graduates%20into%20the%20workforce.%20The%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchina-economy-real-youth-unemployment-rate-50-percent-lie-flat-2023-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eyouth%20unemployment%20rate%20in%20China%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20those%20aged%2016%20to%2024%20rose%20to%20a%20record%2021%25%20as%20of%20May%202023%2C%20up%20from%2015.4%25%20two%20years%20prior.%20That's%20compared%20to%20the%20US%20youth%20unemployment%20rate%20of%207.4%25%20in%20May.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20could%20cause%20diminished%20productivity%20in%20China%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Ewhich%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Ecould%20strain%20the%20US%20because%20it%20is%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fapps.bea.gov%2Finternational%2Ffactsheet%2Ffactsheet.html%23650%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehighly%20dependent%20on%20China%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20goods%20and%20services.%20Despite%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchina-trade-war-covid-companies-moving-supply-chains-2022-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esome%20efforts%20to%20decouple%20from%20China%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20it's%20still%20the%20third%20largest%20export%20market%20for%20the%20US%2C%20and%20American%20companies%20earn%20billions%20of%20dollars%20annually%20from%20sales%20in%20China.%20In%202022%2C%20US%20exports%20to%20China%20were%20%24197.3%20billion%2C%20up%202.8%25%20from%202021%2C%20and%20imports%20from%20China%20were%20%24563.6%20billion%2C%20up%207.1%25%20from%202021.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20the%20heels%20of%20high%20youth%20unemployment%20numbers%20in%20May%2C%20China's%20government%20later%20announced%20it%20would%20no%20longer%20be%20publishing%20those%20statistics%2C%20with%20a%20spokesperson%20of%20the%20National%20Bureau%20of%20Statistics%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2023%2F08%2F15%2Fbusiness%2Fchina-youth-unemployment.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esaying%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20August%20that%20the%20surveys%20researchers%20use%20to%20collect%20the%20data%20%26quot%3Bneed%20to%20be%20further%20improved%20and%20optimized.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20announcement%20that%20the%20data%20would%20no%20longer%20be%20published%20drew%20criticism%20and%20sarcasm%20on%20China's%20social%20media%20site%20Weibo%2C%20with%20one%20user%20saying%3A%20%26quot%3BPut%20in%20a%20clearer%20way%2C%20the%20current%20data%20looks%20very%20bad%2C%20so%20don't%20look%20at%20it%20for%20now.%26quot%3B%20And%20not%20only%20does%20it%20look%20bad%20for%20China%20%E2%80%94Benn%20Steil%2C%20senior%20fellow%20and%20director%20of%20international%20economics%20at%20the%20Council%20on%20Foreign%20Relations%2C%20told%20Insider%2C%20%26quot%3Bit%20obviously%20is%20going%20to%20have%20an%20impact%20on%20the%20rest%20of%20world.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BChina%20is%20really%20facing%20a%20crisis%20in%20terms%20of%20its%20ability%20to%20boost%20productivity%20growth%2C%26quot%3B%20Steil%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20noted%20that%20well-educated%20Chinese%20youth%20are%20overwhelmingly%20expecting%20to%20go%20into%20service%20sector%20jobs%20like%20computer%20science%20rather%20than%20manufacturing%20%E2%80%94%20and%20there%20are%20not%20enough%20available%20jobs%20in%20the%20former%20sector%2C%20so%20those%20graduates'%20skills%20are%20not%20being%20put%20to%20use.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20fact%20that%20there%20aren't%20these%20jobs%20in%20the%20service%20sector%20is%20a%20direct%20result%20of%20bad%20national%20economic%20management%20in%20China%2C%26quot%3B%20Steil%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20added%20that%20as%20long%20as%20%26quot%3Bbad%20economic%20policy%20is%20China%26quot%3B%20is%20stunting%20productivity%2C%20there%20will%20be%20%26quot%3Bsignificantly%20fewer%20export%20opportunities%20for%20US%20companies.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAdditionally%2C%20as%20senior%20lecturer%20at%20Victoria%20University%20of%20Wellington%20Christian%20Yao%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheconversation.com%2Fchinas-youth-unemployment-problem-has-become-a-crisis-we-can-no-longer-ignore-213751%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewrote%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20a%20recent%20commentary%20piece%2C%20a%20prolonged%20youth%20unemployment%20crisis%20in%20China%20could%20trigger%20civil%20unrest%2C%20impacting%20international%20relations%20by%20threatening%20to%20destabilize%20trade%20and%20supply%20chains.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20June%20report%20from%20the%20think%20tank%20China%20Macroeconomy%20Forum%20said%20that%20the%20crisis%20could%20persist%20over%20the%20next%20decade%20and%20intensify%20in%20the%20short%20term%2C%20and%20there's%20significant%20improvement%20to%20be%20done%20in%20ensuring%20the%20skillsets%20college%20graduates%20earn%20match%20the%20jobs%20available.%20A%20New%20York%20Times%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2023%2F08%2F15%2Fbusiness%2Fchina-youth-unemployment.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etranslation%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20the%20June%20report%20said%3A%20%26quot%3BIf%20it%20is%20not%20handled%20properly%2C%20it%20will%20cause%20other%20social%20problems%20beyond%20the%20economy%2C%20and%20it%20could%20even%20ignite%20the%20fuse%20of%20political%20problems.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EWhy%20youth%20have%20such%20a%20big%20impact%20on%20the%20economy%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ECompare%20China's%20situation%20to%20the%20US's%20own%20jobs-skills%20mismatch%20at%20the%20height%20of%20the%20pandemic%20when%20there%20were%20too%20many%20jobs%20available%2C%20despite%20millions%20of%20unemployed%20workers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20difference%20is%20that%20workers%20in%20the%20US%20were%20able%20to%20exercise%20some%20power%20to%20negotiate%20higher%20wages%20in%20industries%20like%20labor%20and%20hospitality%2C%20and%20therefore%20fill%20the%20labor%20shortages.%20The%20reason%20that's%20not%20happening%20in%20China%20is%20because%20its%20government%20is%20not%20making%20an%20effort%20to%20expand%20jobs%20in%20the%20service%20sector%2C%20instead%20investing%20in%20sectors%20like%20property%20and%20construction%20that%20have%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cfr.org%2Fblog%2Fchina-buckles-under-zero-covid-xi-bets-big-bloat%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehistorically%20been%20unproductive%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Steil%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAdditionally%2C%20nearly%20three%20years%20of%20on-off%20COVID-19%20lockdowns%2C%20the%20pandemic's%20hit%20on%20the%20economy%2C%20and%20the%20current%20downturn%20have%20hit%20young%20people's%20confidence%20in%20China's%20public%20governance%20and%20created%20a%20sense%20of%20disenchantment%2C%20Alfred%20Wu%2C%20an%20associate%20professor%20at%20the%20National%20University%20of%20Singapore's%20Lee%20Kuan%20Yew%20School%20of%20Public%20Policy%2C%20told%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20think%20people%20have%20given%20up%20believing%20in%20the%20whole%20structure%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Wu%2C%20referring%20to%20the%20governance%20and%20economic%20systems%20in%20China.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWu%20thinks%20China's%20youths%20%E2%80%94%20like%20those%20of%20Japan%20in%20the%201990s%20after%20an%20asset-price%20bubble%20from%201986%20to%201991%20popped%20%E2%80%94%20may%20be%20entering%20into%20a%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fjapan-millennial-salaryman-job-wages-rent-home-ownership-birthrate-2023-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%20%26quot%3BLost%20Decade%26quot%3B%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20economic%20stagnation%20and%20price%20deflation%2C%20which%20contributes%20to%20their%20disillusionment%20and%20a%20loss%20in%20direction.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGoldman%20Sachs%20researchers%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.goldmansachs.com%2Fintelligence%2Fpages%2Fwhy-has-youth-unemployment-risen-so-much-in-china.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewrote%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20a%20May%20note%20that%20young%20people%20are%20particularly%20vulnerable%20in%20economic%20downturns%20like%20the%20one%20China%20is%20having%20because%20they%20have%20less%20work%20experience%20%E2%80%94%20and%20a%20mismatch%20between%20the%20skills%20they%20acquired%20and%20the%20jobs%20available%20means%20they're%20even%20more%20vulnerable%20to%20uncertainty.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20stakes%20are%20high%20for%20correcting%20these%20imbalances%2C%20given%20how%20important%20the%20youth%20population%20is%20to%20China's%20economy%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20note%20said.%20%26quot%3BThis%20cohort%20spends%20heavily%20in%20areas%20such%20as%20culture%20and%20education%2C%20rent%2C%20transportation%20and%20communication.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGiven%20many%20recent%20college%20graduates%20in%20China%20cannot%20find%20employment%20in%20the%20areas%20in%20which%20they%20studied%2C%20they're%20turning%20to%20other%20options%2C%20like%20becoming%20%26quot%3Bfull-time%20children%26quot%3B%20%E2%80%94%20a%20phrase%20that%20became%20popular%20on%20social%20media%20site%20Douban%20last%20year%20referring%20to%20adult%20children%20who%20stay%20at%20home%20with%20their%20parents%20and%20perform%20households%20tasks%20because%20they%20cannot%20find%20a%20job%20elsewhere.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20%26quot%3Bfull-time%20child%26quot%3B%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nbcnews.com%2Fnews%2Fworld%2Fchina-youth-unemployment-full-time-children-rcna91813%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etold%3C%2Fa%3E%20NBC%20News%20that%20%26quot%3Bif%20my%20business%20had%20been%20very%20successful%2C%20I%20probably%20wouldn't%20have%20become%20a%20full-time%20daughter.%20It%20is%20an%20involuntary%20decision%2C%20but%20it%20is%20an%20option.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStill%2C%20it's%20not%20a%20permanent%20solution.%20Steil%20said%20that%20the%20longer%20China%20cannot%20employ%20the%20growing%20number%20of%20young%20people%20that%20are%20graduating%20from%20college%20each%20year%2C%20it'll%20hurt%20the%20economy%20in%20a%20time%20when%20China%20cannot%20afford%20to%20be%20even%20more%20destabilized.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20young%20people%20in%20China%20can't%20get%20productive%20opportunities%20within%20the%20country%2C%20we%20may%20see%20mass%20emigration%2C%20we%20may%20see%20a%20pickup%20once%20again%20in%20Chinese%20student%20numbers%20in%20the%20United%20States%2C%20and%20we%20may%20see%20the%20Chinese%20choosing%20not%20only%20to%20study%20abroad%2C%20but%20to%20stay%20abroad.%20And%20that's%20not%20something%20that%20China%20should%20welcome%2C%26quot%3B%20Steil%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20unemployment%20crisis%20is%20%26quot%3Bdisproportionately%20affecting%20the%20younger%20segment%20of%20its%20population%2C%20and%20this%20is%20really%20China's%20future%2C%26quot%3B%20Steil%20said.%20%26quot%3BSo%20it's%20a%20big%20problem.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchina-xi-jinping-economy-youth-unemployment-crisis-impact-on-us-2023-10%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1698577441000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6537e0d3356802a56be22369%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchina-xi-jinping-economy-youth-unemployment-crisis-impact-on-us-2023-10%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22China's%20youth%20are%20choosing%20to%20be%20%26quot%3Bfull-time%20children%26quot%3B%20instead%20of%20entering%20the%20workforce%20after%20college.%20It's%20bad%20for%20China's%20economy%2C%20and%20the%20world.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22asheffey%40businessinsider.com%20(Ayelet%20Sheffey%2CHuileng%20Tan)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A10%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchina-xi-jinping-economy-youth-unemployment-crisis-impact-on-us-2023-10%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3