0from%20the%20local%20police%20force.%20A%20Karnataka%20High%20Court%20judgment%20in%20January%202022%20currently%20allows%20protests%20only%20at%20Freedom%20park%20in%20Bengaluru.%20However%2C%20as%20far%20as%20pro-Palestine%20protests%20go%2C%20the%20police%20have%20been%20swiftly%20denying%20permissions%20for%20demonstrations%20and%20registering%20First%20Information%20Reports%20against%20peaceful%20protestors.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20Bengaluru%20police%20have%20rejected%20as%20many%20as%20three%20petitions%20seeking%20permission%20to%20protest%20at%20Freedom%20Park%20in%20solidarity%20with%20Palestine-%20and%20have%20given%20different%20excuses%20for%20the%20rejection.%20Two%20applications%20by%20Left%20parties%20%E2%80%94%20the%20Communist%20Party%20of%20India%20(Marxist)%20and%20the%20Socialist%20Unity%20Centre%20of%20India%20were%20rejected%20citing%20%E2%80%9Climited%20space%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20latest%20and%20the%20third%20instance%20is%20the%20denial%20of%20permission%20by%20the%20Deputy%20Commissioner%20of%20Police%20(West)%20to%20a%20coalition%20of%20civil%20society%20groups%20on%20the%20ground%20that%20protesting%20in%20solidarity%20with%20Palestinians%20was%20an%20%E2%80%9Cinternational%20issue%E2%80%9D.%20The%20letter%20from%20DCP%20S%20Girish%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9CSince%20you%20have%20requested%20permission%20to%20hold%20a%20protest%20in%20relation%20to%20international%20issues%20in%20the%20petition%20letter%2C%20the%20permission%20has%20been%20denied%20for%20the%20protest%20on%2028-10-2023%20in%20the%20interest%20of%20maintaining%20law%20and%20order.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%20data-test-id%3D%5C%22text%5C%22%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20police%20have%20also%20detained%20and%20registered%20FIRs%20against%20protestors%20for%20expressing%20solidarity%20with%20Palestine.%20In%20Bengaluru%2C%20two%20FIRs%20were%20lodged%20following%20a%20gathering%20of%20activists%20and%20civil%20society%20members%20at%20the%20MG%20Road%20Metro%20Station%20on%20October%2016%2C%20where%20they%20called%20for%20India%20to%20condemn%20Israel%E2%80%99s%20attack%20on%20Palestine.%20As%20many%20as%2030%20activists%20were%20picked%20up%20by%20the%20police%20and%20detained%20in%20Ashok%20Nagar%20and%20Cubbon%20Park%20police%20stations.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EA%2058-year-old%20man%20in%20Mangaluru%20was%20arrested%20for%20a%20video%20in%20which%20he%20appealed%20for%20prayers%20for%20Hamas.%20In%20Hosapete%2C%20a%2020-year-old%20youth%20was%20detained%20for%20sharing%20a%20pro-Palestine%20status%20on%20WhatsApp.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%20data-test-id%3D%5C%22text%5C%22%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%20response%20to%20the%20police%20clampdown%2C%20Bengaluru%20for%20Justice%20and%20Peace%2C%20a%20coalition%20of%20civil%20society%20groups%20has%20written%20a%20letter%20to%20Chief%20Minister%20Siddaramaiah%2C%20demanding%20the%20right%20to%20protest%20and%20assemble%20peacefully.%20The%20letter%20highlighted%20the%20paradox%20of%20police%20registering%20FIRs%20against%20peaceful%20protesters%20for%20holding%20protests%20outside%20Freedom%20Park%2C%20while%20simultaneously%20denying%20permissions%20to%20protest%20within%20the%20park%20itself.%20%E2%80%9CSuch%20actions%20of%20the%20Karnataka%20state%20government%20is%20not%20only%20an%20assault%20on%20the%20fundamental%20rights%20of%20citizens%20to%20protest%2C%20but%20also%20display%20a%20cruel%20indifference%20to%20the%20genocide%20being%20carried%20out%20by%20the%20Israeli%20government%2C%20and%20is%20an%20immoral%20abuse%20of%20power%20by%20these%20offices%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20letter%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20title%3D%5C%22Across%20India%2C%20People%20Face%20Charges%20for%20Participating%20in%20Protests%20in%20Support%20of%20Palestine%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Findia-palestine-protests-police-crackdown%5C%22%3EAcross%20India%2C%20People%20Face%20Charges%20for%20Participating%20in%20Protests%20in%20Support%20of%20Palestine%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EActivists%20questioned%20the%20Karnataka%20government%E2%80%99s%20stance%2C%20highlighting%20that%20other%20states%20have%20permitted%20large%20rallies%20and%20protests%20in%20solidarity%20with%20Palestine%2C%20while%20Karnataka%20has%20chosen%20to%20stifle%20such%20expressions%20of%20support.%20Recently%2C%20a%20mega%20rally%20was%20held%20by%20the%20Indian%20Union%20Muslim%20League%20in%20Kerala%20and%20several%20thousands%20participated.%20The%20letter%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9CWe%2C%20members%20of%20Bengaluru%20for%20Justice%20and%20Peace%2C%20strongly%20believe%20that%20the%20reasons%20furnished%20by%20the%20police%20in%20their%20letter%20rejecting%20permission%20for%20our%20protest%20are%20insufficient%20and%20unsubstantiated%2C%20to%20say%20the%20least.%20We%20are%20shocked%20at%20the%20deliberate%20attempt%20to%20silence%20our%20voices%20in%20support%20of%20Palestine%2C%20when%20the%20Congress%20Party%20as%20well%20the%20Union%20government%20have%20issued%20statements%20in%20support%20of%20the%20Palestinian%20people.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EActivists%20also%20highlighted%20the%20statements%20issued%20by%20political%20parties%20at%20both%20the%20state%20and%20national%20level%2C%20expressing%20solidarity%20with%20the%20Palestinian%20people.%20They%20argue%20that%20the%20actions%20of%20the%20Karnataka%20government%20and%20police%20stand%20in%20stark%20contrast%20to%20these%20statements%2C%20creating%20a%20dissonance%20in%20the%20approach%20towards%20the%20Israel-Palestine%20conflict.%20%E2%80%9CWhy%20is%20the%20Karnataka%20government%20deliberately%20silencing%20voices%20of%20solidarity%20with%20the%20Palestinian%20people%3F%20Why%20is%20the%20Karnataka%20police%20filing%20FIRs%20against%20those%20seeking%20an%20end%20to%20Israeli%20occupation%3F%E2%80%9D%20the%20activists%20questioned.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ESince%20October%207%2C%20Israel%20and%20Hamas%2C%20a%20Palestine-based%20militant%20group%2C%20have%20been%20engaged%20in%20a%20war%20that%20has%20taken%20several%20thousand%20lives.%20The%20crisis%20is%20being%20described%20as%20the%20most%20severe%20security%20situation%20in%20the%20region%20in%20the%20last%20five%20decades.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20article%20was%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thenewsminute.com%2Fkarnataka%2Fbengaluru-police-stifle-pro-palestine-protests-with-denial-of-permission-firs%5C%22%3Eoriginally%20published%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%3C%2Fem%3E%20The%20News%20Minute.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1698556307000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F29104106%2FScreenshot-2023-10-29-at-10.40.33-AM.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Fbengaluru-police-stifle-pro-palestine-protests-with-denial-of-permission-firs%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20Bengaluru%20police%20have%20rejected%20as%20many%20as%20three%20petitions%20seeking%20permission%20to%20protest%20at%20Freedom%20Park%20in%20solidarity%20with%20Palestine%20%E2%80%93%20and%20have%20given%20different%20excuses%20for%20the%20rejection.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A15%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Fbengaluru-police-stifle-pro-palestine-protests-with-denial-of-permission-firs%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22%E2%80%98Saturday%20Night%20Live%E2%80%99%20Pays%20Tribute%20to%20Matthew%20Perry%20Hours%20After%20His%20Death%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1698555949000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fvariety.com%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2FMatthew-Perry-SNL.png%3Fw%3D1000%26h%3D563%26crop%3D1%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fvariety.com%2F%3Fp%3D1235772037%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22%E2%80%9CSaturday%20Night%20Live%E2%80%9D%20paid%20tribute%20to%20Matthew%20Perry%2C%20hours%20after%20the%20news%20of%20his%20death%20broke.%2